we give up on that?

00:38:11.210 --> 00:38:13.480
IVAN PAULINO-LIMA:
So this is a matter

00:38:13.480 --> 00:38:19.930
of debate, actually, for all
these missions, human missions

00:38:19.930 --> 00:38:21.360
to Mars.

00:38:21.360 --> 00:38:24.280
We know that any
human mission to Mars

00:38:24.280 --> 00:38:26.920
will eventually
contaminate Mars.

00:38:26.920 --> 00:38:27.540
That we know.

00:38:27.540 --> 00:38:29.890
This is something
that we know for sure.

00:38:29.890 --> 00:38:34.770
And I think in the past, the
protocols for sterilization

00:38:34.770 --> 00:38:38.450
of spacecraft, they were not
as rigid as they are today.

00:38:38.450 --> 00:38:42.530
We think that some of the
earlier missions sent to Mars

00:38:42.530 --> 00:38:46.460
may have carried some
bio-burden on Mars.

00:38:46.460 --> 00:38:48.760
But we think that
this bio-burden

00:38:48.760 --> 00:38:52.650
won't do anything there, because
the environment is so hostile.

00:38:52.650 --> 00:38:56.230
There's no water,
a lot of radiation.

00:38:56.230 --> 00:39:00.810
It's very hard to think of
any type of growth there.

00:39:00.810 --> 00:39:03.560
So I think it's
currently being decided.

00:39:03.560 --> 00:39:06.230
It is an ethical question
if we have the right

00:39:06.230 --> 00:39:11.630
to go to another planet knowing
that contamination will happen.

00:39:11.630 --> 00:39:15.580
And it is interesting
to note that the most

00:39:15.580 --> 00:39:18.820
interesting places
to detect life, which

00:39:18.820 --> 00:39:22.650
are the aquifers, places
where there is more water,

00:39:22.650 --> 00:39:25.770
are also the best places for
humans to go there and make

00:39:25.770 --> 00:39:28.620
use of those resources.

00:39:28.620 --> 00:39:38.350
But we are still
debating, actually,

00:39:38.350 --> 00:39:41.660
what are the implications
of contaminating Mars,

00:39:41.660 --> 00:39:44.612
the extent we accept that.

00:39:44.612 --> 00:39:45.800
This is a matter of debate.

00:39:45.800 --> 00:39:50.520
We recently had a meeting,
I think last year at NASA,

00:39:50.520 --> 00:39:51.520
to debate that.

00:39:51.520 --> 00:39:54.910
It was called Planetary
Protection on knowledge gaps

00:39:54.910 --> 00:39:56.780
that we have in this area.

00:39:56.780 --> 00:40:04.120
So I think we cannot give up
on exploration just with fear

00:40:04.120 --> 00:40:08.210
of contaminating stuff, because
if this is a matter of our own

00:40:08.210 --> 00:40:12.720
survival, then I think it puts
a lot of weight on the ethical

00:40:12.720 --> 00:40:14.540
debate.

