00:42:06.890 --> 00:42:09.860
AUDIENCE: So
maganese-containing compounds

00:42:09.860 --> 00:42:12.920
is not the only
antioxidant then obviously.

00:42:12.920 --> 00:42:17.240
Any reasons this seems
to be particularly chosen

00:42:17.240 --> 00:42:20.780
for these bacteria?

00:42:20.780 --> 00:42:22.340
IVAN PAULINO-LIMA:
Well, of course,

00:42:22.340 --> 00:42:25.830
any organisms that are
resistant to radiation

00:42:25.830 --> 00:42:28.760
have to have
genetic information.

00:42:28.760 --> 00:42:32.820
So the basic machinery to repair
the DNA needs to be there.

00:42:32.820 --> 00:42:36.430
And the information needs
to be encoded by DNA.

00:42:36.430 --> 00:42:41.510
But I think late '90s,
beginning of the 2000s,

00:42:41.510 --> 00:42:44.790
people started to think of other
factors, physiological factors.

00:42:44.790 --> 00:42:47.890
And they tested different
things, different compounds,

00:42:47.890 --> 00:42:50.630
different metals, different
nutrients that could

00:42:50.630 --> 00:42:52.280
affect radiation resistance.

00:42:52.280 --> 00:42:55.170
And then they started to see
that organisms that accumulate

00:42:55.170 --> 00:42:58.410
high manganese had
these trend of being

00:42:58.410 --> 00:43:00.320
resistant to radiation.

00:43:00.320 --> 00:43:03.140
And just in the
past few years, that

00:43:03.140 --> 00:43:08.060
has been elucidated that these
manganese complexes helps

00:43:08.060 --> 00:43:11.300
to protect the proteins
against oxidation.

00:43:11.300 --> 00:43:13.780
And then the proteins
remain active

00:43:13.780 --> 00:43:15.550
and can do the DNA repair.

00:43:15.550 --> 00:43:17.580
And in fact,
Deinococcus radiodurans

00:43:17.580 --> 00:43:21.830
is specialized in
double-strand break repair.

00:43:21.830 --> 00:43:26.440
Compared to other organisms, it
lacks a few genes of DNA repair

00:43:26.440 --> 00:43:30.820
to oxidative damage like
UV-A and UV-B generates

00:43:30.820 --> 00:43:33.280
a lot of oxidative stress.

00:43:33.280 --> 00:43:37.150
And Deinococcus is as
resistant as E. coli.

00:43:37.150 --> 00:43:39.770
It is sensitive
to UV-A and UV-B,

00:43:39.770 --> 00:43:42.220
because it's more specialized
for double-strand break

00:43:42.220 --> 00:43:43.060
resistance.

00:43:43.060 --> 00:43:46.020
So that's what
motivates us to seek

00:43:46.020 --> 00:43:48.900
for a more complete set of
genes on an organism that

00:43:48.900 --> 00:43:52.390
has a more complete set
of genes or strategies

00:43:52.390 --> 00:43:54.390
to survive high
doses of radiation

00:43:54.390 --> 00:43:56.080
and also to
understand better how

00:43:56.080 --> 00:43:59.830
we can transfer this capability
to humans in the future.

